            The main source for the biographical data collected and presented in the JSN is the twelve-volume
            &quot;Biblioth&egrave;que de la Compagnie de J&eacute;sus&quot;. Using Harris' list of topics considered
            Jesuit science, one can
            identify approximately 1000 names of interest in the Biblioth&egrave;que. Several other works, mostly with a
            specific regional focus, provide further biographical details or even add people not covered by the
            Biblioth&egrave;que.
        </p>

